# Model weights — huge binaries, never in git.
# NOTE: anchored to the repo root (/models/) — an unanchored `models/` also matches the panel's
# source dir control/Models/ (case-insensitive on Windows), which silently dropped Status.cs from
# git and broke CI / fresh-clone builds. The *.gguf/*.safetensors/*.bin patterns below are the real
# backstop for stray weight files anywhere in the tree.
/models/
*.gguf
*.safetensors
*.bin

# llama.cpp / tool binaries dropped into the repo
serving/llama.cpp/
*.exe
*.dll

# Logs, scratch, scorecards-in-progress
*.log
tmp/
.scratch/
.tmp-*           # root-level render/verify scratch (e.g. panel `--render .tmp-studio.png`)

# doki control plane runtime (PID files + logs)
.run/

# Local media-gen install — SwarmUI + ComfyUI backend + image/video model weights
media/

# Local TTS install — Chatterbox-TTS-Server repo + cu128 venv + voice model weights
tts/

# Local STT install — onnx-asr venv + Parakeet model cache
stt/

# Memory MCP runtime database
serving/memory-mcp/*.db

# Python caches
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Editor/OS noise
.vscode/
.idea/
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Claude Code harness artifacts
.claude/

# .NET build artifacts
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/

# control-panel generated previews / screen captures — NOT the tracked build inputs.
# control/assets/dokidex.ico, splash.png and panel-hero.png ARE required/curated (ApplicationIcon +
# native SplashScreen + README hero, regenerated via `dotnet run -- --render`) and must stay committed;
# only the heavy/throwaway *-preview.png / boot-capture renders are ignored.
control/assets/boot-capture.png
control/assets/*-preview.png

# generated, machine-specific launcher shortcut (created per-machine by control.bat / `doki panel`,
# with an absolute TargetPath) — never commit it.
DokiDex.lnk
